value.0: The bulk of the bottom of this stone plaque is worn away, but the phrase etched within remains.
"A pebble will stay dry inside, no matter how long it is submerged in a pool of water"  ...
"We still hone the axe which slew your kin. Tis' still sharp and ever-ready"
"The Humans have a saying. The nail that sticks out gets hammered. We have a saying too. Humans do shoddy work"
"You can kill a dwarf, but you can never vanquish one"
"It is easy to fool a goblin, but even easier to kill one."
"Rest your shields, lean on stones, listen and always remember, long are the arms and legs of men, yet still longer, the Dwarven members!"
"Marriage is like an anvil. It is always there. It is solid. It is quiet. Like a husband."
"Dwarven women are like axes. As dangerous from the back as from the front"
"Drinking contests with humans are unbearable. They drink, they collapse, and we have to drag them back to their homes. The next day they never remember losing."
:The stones will sing if you let them"
"Leave iron to rest before you hammer it"
"You are softer than sandstone and drier than talc"
